=== Singles ===
{{Listen
|filename=Luis Miguel - Por Debajo De La Mesa.ogg
|title=Luis Miguel "Por Debajo de la Mesa" (1997)
|description=A sample of the lead single "Por Debajo de la Mesa", an original composition for the album by Armando Manzanero.
|format=[[Ogg]]
}}
"Por Debajo de la Mesa"  was released as the [[lead single]] from the album. The single was released for [[radio airplay]] on July 15, 1997, and reached number one on the [[Hot Latin Songs|''Billboard'' Hot Latin Songs]] chart two months later; it would spend twenty-six weeks on the chart.<ref>{{cite news |title= Llega a todo el mundo 'Por Debajo de la Mesa|first=Carlos |last= Meraz|url=http://busquedas.gruporeforma.com/reforma/Pages/BuscaImpresa.aspx|newspaper= El Norte|publisher=Grupo Reforma|date= 1997-07-15|accessdate=2011-03-28|language=Spanish}}{{subscription required}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Por Debajo de la Mesa &nbsp;<U+2014> Luis Miguel |url=http://www.billboard.com/#/song/luis-miguel/por-debajo-de-la-mesa/1018185 |date=1997-09-06|accessdate=2011-02-19 |work=Billboard |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]}}</ref> A [[music video]] was made for the song.<ref>{{cite video |people= Miguel, Luis (actor, singer) |title= Por Debajo de la Mesa by Luis Miguel Music Video on Yahoo! Music|url= http://new.music.yahoo.com/luis-miguel/videos/view/por-debajo-de-la-mesa--2144862;_ylt=AmXYUy_4cgPDWk5zWer82BDHxCUv|medium= Music video|language= Spanish|publisher=[[Yahoo! Music]] |accessdate=2011-02-19}}</ref> The second single released, "El Reloj" ("The Clock"), reached number two on the Hot Latin Songs chart,<ref>{{cite web|title=El Reloj&nbsp;<U+2014> Luis Miguel |url=http://www.billboard.com/#/song/luis-miguel/por-debajo-de-la-mesa/1018185 |date=1997-11-08|accessdate=2011-02-19 |work=Billboard |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]}}</ref> as did the third single, "Contigo (Estar Contigo").<ref>{{cite web|title=Contigo (Estar contigo) <U+2013> Luis Miguel |url=http://www.billboard.com/#/song/luis-miguel/contigo-estar-contigo/1018190 |date=1998-01-24|accessdate=2011-02-19 |work=Billboard |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]}}</ref> "De Quererte Asi (De T'Avoir Aimee)" peaked at number twenty-three on the Hot Latin Songs chart,<ref>{{cite web|title=De Quererte Asi (De T'Avoir Aimee)&nbsp;<U+2014> Luis Miguel |url=http://www.billboard.com/#/song/luis-miguel/de-quererte-asi-de-t-avoir-aimee/3338986 |date=1998-04-18|accessdate=2011-02-19 |work=Billboard |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]}}</ref> while "Sabor a Mi" ("Taste From Me") peaked at number six after its release.<ref>{{cite web|title=El Reloj&nbsp;<U+2014> Luis Miguel |url=http://www.billboard.com/#/song/luis-miguel/sabor-a-mi/1018184 |date=1998-07-11|accessdate=2011-02-19 |work=Billboard |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]}}</ref> All of the singles, including "B<U+00E9>same Mucho" ("Kiss Me More"), were number one on radio stations across Latin America.<ref name="esmas"/>

== Promotion ==
{{main|Romances Tour}}

Miguel launched his [[Romances Tour]], consisting of 84 concerts, in Las Vegas, Nevada, on September 12, 1997. The performances featured Miguel performing dance-pop and bolero arrangements for two-and-a-half hours.<ref name="hilburn">{{cite web
|last= Hilburn
|first = Robert
|date=1997-09-20
|title= Luis Miguel's Crossroads
|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1997/sep/20/entertainment/ca-34128/3
|page=3
|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]
|publisher=Tribune Company
|accessdate=2011-04-15}}</ref>  Adam Sandler of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' expressed a mixed reaction to the concert in the [[Universal Amphitheatre]] in Los Angeles, California. He noted that Miguel rarely acknowledged his audience or ventured out from center stage.<ref>{{cite web
|last= Sandler
|first = Adam
|date=1997-09-22
|title= Variety Review <U+2013> Luis Miguel
|url=http://www.variety.com/review/VE1117436847?refCatId=34
|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]
|publisher=[[Reed Business Information]]
|accessdate=2011-04-03}}</ref> Robert Hilburn of the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' had a more positive reaction, which he described as a "marvelously designed and wonderfully executed blend of Latin music tradition".<ref name="hilburn"/> Another Times contributor, Ernesto Lechner, wrote that Miguel's bolero performance at the [[Arrowhead Pond]] arena in California "brought the house down" and stated that the experience at the concert was "pretty close" to [[Beatlemania]].<ref>{{cite web
|last= Lechner
|first = Ernesto
|date=1998-02-28
|title= Luis Miguel's Crossroads
|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1998/feb/28/entertainment/ca-23784
|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]
|publisher=Tribune Company
|accessdate=2011-04-18}}</ref> In New York City, Miguel performed five consecutive shows in the [[Radio City Music Hall]]. In [[Mexico City]] he performed seventeen consecutive concerts in the [[National Auditorium]], where it was the highest-grossing concert by a Latin artist that year.<ref name="jan1998">
{{cite journal
| last = Lannert
| first = John
| date = 1998-01-10
| title = Latin Notas: En Concierto
| journal = Billboard
| publisher = Nielsen Business Media, Inc.
| volume = 110
| issue = 2
| page = 26
| url = http://books.google.com/books?id=ug0EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA26&dq=%22romances%22+%22luis+miguel%22+intitle:billboard#v=onepage&q&f=false
| accessdate = 2011-06-15}}</ref> The tour also traveled to South America; including [[Chile]], and Argentina; and continued until May 1998, when Miguel performed throughout Spain.<ref name="terra">{{cite web
|title=Biograf<U+00ED>a de Luis Miguel 
|url=http://www.terra.com.mx/articulo.aspx?articuloid=972048
|language=Spanish
|work=[[Terra Networks]]
|publisher=[[Telef<U+00F3>nica]]
|date=2010-10-05
|accessdate=2011-04-19}}</ref> Miguel was the first Latin artist to be inducted to the ''Pollstar'' "Top 20 All-Time Grossing Tours" for most tickets sold for consecutive concerts at one venue in 1997.<ref name="esmas">{{cite web
|title= Biograf<U+00ED>a de Luis Miguel
|url=http://www.esmas.com/espectaculos/artistas/280998.html
|language=Spanish
|work=[[Esmas.com]]
|publisher=[[Televisa]]
|accessdate=2011-02-19}}</ref>

